      "id": "PopularPost38771",
      "post_content": "I think it works best in a counterspell deck. With an Orrery in play, I never play cards during my turn, only during theirs. This way I've always got mana spare for counters, and if they don't play anything worth countering I can play my creatures at the end of their turn.",
