      "id": "PopularPost57201",
      "post_content": " Also fun with [Progentius](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Progentius) and [Angelic Renewal](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Angelic Renewal). [Elvish Piper](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Elvish Piper), [Natural Order](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Natural Order), [Fist of the Suns](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Fist of the Suns) etc..are some potentially fast ways to get him out.\n  \n   \nI like the idea of instant discard :).\n  \n   \n On another note its fun to have [Isochron Scepter](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Isochron Scepter) + cmc <2 discard instant or sorcerry such as [Hymn to Tourach](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Hymn to Tourach) and maybe a [Vedalken Orrery](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Vedalken Orrery) + perhaps something like [Teferi, Mage of Zhalfir](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Teferi, Mage of Zhalfir )  that way you can lock them out of their draw (by using Isochron Scepter's Hymn to Tourach at the end of your opponent's draw step) completely if all previously made cards are still unhampered with. For Multiplayer [Seedborn Muse](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Seedborn Muse) or something like it would help to lock out all others besides yourself or yourself too if you want.\n  \n   \n\"Will this allow transmute cards to be transmuted whenever an instant c... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "originalcardtext",
